title: Alexandria Sydney factory fire forces residents to be evacuated as it spreads to nearby buildings
text:
Five people have been evacuated as firefighters battle to put out a huge factory blaze in inner Sydney that has spread to adjoining buildings.

Emergency services were called to Alexandria at about 2.15am on Tuesday, where they found the factory well alight.

About 25 fire trucks and 90 firefighters crews are trying to extinguish the blaze, which spread to adjoining buildings.

Emergency services were called to Alexandria about 2.15am on Tuesday where they found the factory well alight (pictured)

About 25 fire trucks and 90 firefighters crews (pictured) are trying to extinguish the blaze, which spread to adjoining buildings

At least five people were evacuated from a nearby unit block.

Witnesses reported seeing flames jumping 60m into the air from the roof of the factory.

No injuries have been reported and the cause of the fire is so far unknown.
description: Emergency services were called to Alexandria, Sydney about 2.15am on Tuesday where they found the factory well alight.
